---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import ProductCard from '../components/ProductCard.astro'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Winter Storm Home Protection Guide"
  description="How to protect your home from winter storms. Covers pipe freeze prevention, heating backup, ice dams, power outages, and emergency preparedness."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="threat-hero">
    <div class="hero-img-wrap">
      <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1511131341194-24e2eeeebb09?w=1600&q=80&fit=crop" alt="House in winter storm" class="hero-img" />
      <div class="hero-overlay"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="container hero-content">
      <div class="hero-label">Winter Storm Preparedness</div>
      <h1>How to Protect Your Home from Winter Storms</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Frozen pipes, ice dams, heating failures, and extended power outages — winter storms
        cause billions in home damage every year. Most of it is preventable.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="#protect" class="btn btn-primary">Protect Your Home</a>
        <a href="#checklist" class="btn btn-secondary">Get the Free Checklist</a>
        <a href="#products" class="btn btn-text">View Recommended Products →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Key facts -->
  <div class="key-facts">
    <div class="container facts-row">
      <div class="fact">
        <div class="fact-value">$5,000+</div>
        <div class="fact-label">Average cost of a frozen pipe claim</div>
      </div>
      <div class="fact-divider"></div>
      <div class="fact">
        <div class="fact-value">20°F</div>
        <div class="fact-label">Temperature when pipes begin to freeze</div>
      </div>
      <div class="fact-divider"></div>
      <div class="fact">
        <div class="fact-value">Ice dams</div>
        <div class="fact-label">Leading cause of winter roof damage</div>
      </div>
      <div class="fact-divider"></div>
      <div class="fact">
        <div class="fact-value">72 hrs</div>
        <div class="fact-label">Prepare to be self-sufficient after a storm</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Tab strip -->
  <nav class="section-tabs">
    <div class="container tabs-row">
      <a href="#risks" class="tab">Winter Risks</a>
      <a href="#pipes" class="tab">Frozen Pipes</a>
      <a href="#heating" class="tab">Heating Backup</a>
      <a href="#icedams" class="tab">Ice Dams</a>
      <a href="#power" class="tab">Power Outages</a>
      <a href="#supplies" class="tab">Emergency Supplies</a>
      <a href="#checklist" class="tab">Free Checklist</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <div class="container page-layout">
    <article class="article">

      <p class="lead">
        Winter storms are deceptive — they look beautiful and feel manageable until your
        pipes burst, your heat fails, or you're without power for four days in subfreezing
        temperatures. The time to prepare is before the first freeze, not during it.
      </p>

      <!-- Part 1 -->
      <div class="part-heading" id="risks">
        <div class="part-number">Part 1</div>
        <h2 class="part-title">Understanding Winter Storm Risk</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="risk-grid">
        <div class="risk-item">
          <div class="risk-icon-wrap">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 48 48" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <path d="M24 8V40M8 24H40M13 13L35 35M35 13L13 35" stroke="#2E7CB8" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              <circle cx="24" cy="24" r="4" fill="#2E7CB8"/>
              <circle cx="24" cy="8" r="2" fill="#2E7CB8"/>
              <circle cx="24" cy="40" r="2" fill="#2E7CB8"/>
              <circle cx="8" cy="24" r="2" fill="#2E7CB8"/>
              <circle cx="40" cy="24" r="2" fill="#2E7CB8"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Frozen Pipes</h3>
          <p>Pipes freeze when temperatures drop below 20°F. A burst pipe releases hundreds of gallons per hour, causing catastrophic damage.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="risk-item">
          <div class="risk-icon-wrap">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 48 48" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <path d="M10 28L24 12L38 28" stroke="#1B3A52" stroke-width="2" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
              <path d="M14 28H34V36H14V28Z" stroke="#1B3A52" stroke-width="2" fill="#EBF4FB"/>
              <path d="M10 32C14 30 18 34 22 32C26 30 30 34 34 32C36 30 38 32 38 32" stroke="#2E7CB8" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Ice Dams</h3>
          <p>Ice builds at roof edges, forcing water under shingles. Can cause thousands in ceiling and wall damage without visible exterior signs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="risk-item">
          <div class="risk-icon-wrap">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 48 48" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <rect x="10" y="20" width="28" height="18" rx="2" stroke="#1B3A52" stroke-width="2" fill="#EBF4FB"/>
              <path d="M16 20V16C16 12.7 19.6 10 24 10C28.4 10 32 12.7 32 16V20" stroke="#1B3A52" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              <path d="M38 14L42 10M38 10L42 14" stroke="#D4691E" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              <circle cx="40" cy="12" r="4" stroke="#D4691E" stroke-width="1.5"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Power Outages</h3>
          <p>Winter storms are the leading cause of power outages. Without heat, pipes freeze and homes become uninhabitable within hours.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="risk-item">
          <div class="risk-icon-wrap">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 48 48" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <path d="M24 8C16 12 12 20 12 28C12 34 17 40 24 40C31 40 36 34 36 28C36 20 32 12 24 8Z" stroke="#1B3A52" stroke-width="2" fill="#EBF4FB"/>
              <path d="M20 28C20 26 22 24 24 24C26 24 28 26 28 28" stroke="#2E7CB8" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              <path d="M24 24V18" stroke="#2E7CB8" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Heating Failure</h3>
          <p>Furnaces fail from overload, gas line issues, or lack of maintenance. A heating failure in a blizzard is a life-safety emergency.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Part 2 -->
      <div class="part-heading" id="protect">
        <div class="part-number">Part 2</div>
        <h2 class="part-title">Protecting Your Home</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="section-block" id="pipes">
        <h2>1. Frozen Pipe Prevention</h2>
        <p>Frozen pipes are the most common and costly winter home emergency. The good news: they're almost entirely preventable with the right preparation.</p>

        <h3>Most Vulnerable Pipes</h3>
        <ul class="action-list">
          <li>Pipes in unheated spaces — garages, crawl spaces, attics, and exterior walls</li>
          <li>Pipes near exterior walls with little insulation</li>
          <li>Outdoor hose bibs and irrigation systems</li>
          <li>Swimming pool supply lines</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Prevention Steps</h3>
        <div class="steps">
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-num">1</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Insulate vulnerable pipes</strong>
              <p>Foam pipe insulation costs under $1 per foot and installs in minutes. Focus on pipes in unheated spaces and exterior walls.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-num">2</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Disconnect and drain outdoor hoses</strong>
              <p>Before the first freeze, disconnect all garden hoses and shut off outdoor water supply valves. Open the outdoor faucet to drain remaining water.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-num">3</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Keep heat at 55°F minimum</strong>
              <p>Even if you're away, never let your home drop below 55°F. The heating cost is far less than a burst pipe claim.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-num">4</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Open cabinet doors during extreme cold</strong>
              <p>Under sinks on exterior walls, open cabinet doors to allow warm air to reach pipes during extreme cold snaps.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="callout callout-red">
          <strong>If a pipe freezes:</strong> Never use an open flame to thaw. Use a hair dryer, heating pad, or warm towels. Know where your main water shutoff is — if a pipe bursts, you have seconds to act.
        </div>

        <div class="product-block" id="products">
          <div class="product-block-header">
            <h3>Pipe Protection Products</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="product-row product-row-2">
            <ProductCard
              name="Frost King Foam Pipe Insulation"
              asin="B000BPIJ56"
              price="$12"
              store="amazon"
              badge="Essential"
              desc="Self-sealing foam insulation for pipes up to 1 inch diameter. Installs in seconds, prevents freezing in unheated spaces. Buy extra."
            />
            <ProductCard
              name="Heat-Line Freeze Protection Cable"
              asin="B07GBKFYQM"
              price="$49"
              store="amazon"
              desc="Self-regulating heat cable wraps around pipes and activates automatically when temperatures drop. For extreme cold or chronic problem pipes."
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="section-block" id="heating">
        <h2>2. Heating Backup</h2>
        <p>Your primary heating system failing during a blizzard is a life-safety emergency, not just a comfort issue. A backup heat source can keep your family safe and prevent pipe damage while you wait for repairs.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-red">
          <strong>Carbon monoxide warning:</strong> Never use propane heaters, gas ranges, or grills indoors for heating. CO poisoning kills within minutes. Only use indoor-rated heating appliances indoors.
        </div>

        <div class="product-block">
          <div class="product-block-header">
            <h3>Backup Heating Options</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="product-row">
            <ProductCard
              name="Mr. Heater Buddy Indoor Propane Heater"
              asin="B002G51BZU"
              price="$89"
              store="amazon"
              badge="Top Pick"
              desc="The most popular indoor-safe propane heater. Heats up to 225 sq ft, has automatic low-oxygen shutoff. Safe for indoor use with ventilation."
            />
            <ProductCard
              name="Vornado MVH Vortex Heater"
              asin="B00JKKVNUM"
              price="$59"
              store="amazon"
              badge="Electric Pick"
              desc="Best electric space heater for whole-room heating. Auto tip-over shutoff, cool-touch exterior, works great for keeping one room warm."
            />
            <ProductCard
              name="DuraHeat Kerosene Heater"
              asin="B07GBKFYQM"
              price="$149"
              store="amazon"
              desc="23,000 BTU kerosene heater warms large spaces without electricity. Good for garages and large rooms during extended outages."
            />
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3>Furnace Maintenance</h3>
        <p>The best backup is a furnace that doesn't fail. Schedule annual furnace maintenance before winter — replace filters, check the heat exchanger, and test the igniter. A $150 tune-up prevents a $3,000 emergency call.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="section-block" id="icedams">
        <h2>3. Ice Dam Prevention</h2>
        <p>Ice dams form when heat escapes through your roof, melts snow, and that water refreezes at the cold eaves. The resulting ice forces water under shingles and into your home.</p>

        <h3>Long-Term Prevention</h3>
        <p>The root cause of ice dams is heat loss through the roof. Proper attic insulation (R-38 to R-60 depending on your climate) and ventilation are the permanent fix. A well-insulated attic stays cold, snow melts uniformly, and ice dams don't form.</p>

        <h3>Immediate Steps</h3>
        <ul class="action-list">
          <li>Use a roof rake to remove snow within 4 feet of the eave after heavy snowfall</li>
          <li>Never use a metal tool or sharp object to chip ice — you'll damage the shingles</li>
          <li>Apply calcium chloride ice melt in a sock across the dam to create drainage channels</li>
          <li>Call a professional if water is actively leaking into your home</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="product-block">
          <div class="product-block-header">
            <h3>Ice Dam Products</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="product-row product-row-2">
            <ProductCard
              name="Avalanche! Original Roof Snow Removal Tool"
              asin="B000BVEPIM"
              price="$69"
              store="amazon"
              badge="Top Rated"
              desc="21-foot wheeled roof rake removes snow safely from the ground. Lightweight aluminum, no ladder required. Most popular roof snow tool."
            />
            <ProductCard
              name="RoofMelt Ice Dam Tablets"
              asin="B001DZRF0I"
              price="$29"
              store="amazon"
              desc="Calcium chloride tablets that melt through ice dams to create drainage channels. Toss on roof — no ladder needed."
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="section-block" id="power">
        <h2>4. Power Outage Preparation</h2>
        <p>Winter power outages are uniquely dangerous because cold temperatures make your home uninhabitable within hours. A generator keeps your heat running — see our full <a href="/generators">generator buying guide</a> for recommendations.</p>

        <div class="steps">
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-num">1</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Know your heating system's power needs</strong>
              <p>Gas furnaces still need electricity to run the blower. A 5,000W generator handles most gas furnaces plus essential circuits.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-num">2</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Have a warm room plan</strong>
              <p>If your heat fails, designate one interior room as the warm room. Close doors, use a safe space heater, and everyone sleeps there.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-num">3</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Know your shutoff locations</strong>
              <p>If pipes freeze and burst, you need to shut off water immediately. Know where your main water shutoff, gas shutoff, and electrical panel are.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="section-block" id="supplies">
        <h2>5. Emergency Supplies</h2>
        <ul class="action-list">
          <li>72-hour supply of food and water (water pipes may freeze)</li>
          <li>Flashlights and extra batteries or a hand-crank lantern</li>
          <li>Battery-powered or hand-crank weather radio</li>
          <li>Extra blankets, sleeping bags, and warm clothing</li>
          <li>First aid kit with a 30-day supply of medications</li>
          <li>Portable phone charger (keep it charged year-round)</li>
          <li>Sand or kitty litter for traction on icy walkways</li>
          <li>Ice scraper and snow brush for your car</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="product-block">
          <div class="product-block-header">
            <h3>Winter Emergency Essentials</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="product-row product-row-2">
            <ProductCard
              name="Midland ER310 Emergency Crank Weather Radio"
              asin="B00A4GE32E"
              price="$59"
              store="amazon"
              badge="Essential"
              desc="NOAA weather alerts, hand crank + solar charging. Works when cell networks and power are both down. Critical for winter storm monitoring."
            />
            <ProductCard
              name="Coleman 1-Burner Propane Stove"
              asin="B00004RA6N"
              price="$49"
              store="amazon"
              desc="Cook hot meals during an extended power outage. Use outdoors or in a well-ventilated space only. Runs on standard 1lb propane cylinders."
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Checklist CTA -->
      <div class="checklist-cta" id="checklist">
        <h2>Free Winter Storm Preparedness Checklist</h2>
        <p>Pipe winterization, heating system checks, emergency supply list, and a pre-storm action plan — all in one download.</p>
        <form class="cta-form" name="winter-checklist" method="POST" data-netlify="true">
          <input type="hidden" name="form-name" value="winter-checklist" />
          <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="your@email.com" required />
          <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Send Me the Checklist</button>
        </form>
      </div>

    </article>

    <aside class="sidebar">
      <div class="sb-card">
        <h4>On This Page</h4>
        <a href="#risks">Winter Risks</a>
        <a href="#pipes">Frozen Pipes</a>
        <a href="#heating">Heating Backup</a>
        <a href="#icedams">Ice Dams</a>
        <a href="#power">Power Outages</a>
        <a href="#supplies">Emergency Supplies</a>
        <a href="#checklist">Free Checklist</a>
      </div>

      <div class="sb-card sb-alert">
        <h4>Act Before First Freeze</h4>
        <p>Pipe insulation, furnace tune-ups, and generator prep should all be done <strong>before</strong> the first cold snap — not during it.</p>
      </div>

      <h4 class="sb-section-label">Related Guides</h4>

      <a href="/generators" class="sb-visual-card">
        <div class="sb-visual-img">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1621905251189-08b45d6a269e?w=300&q=80&fit=crop" alt="Generator guide" />
          <div class="sb-visual-overlay"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="sb-visual-label">Generator Guide →</div>
      </a>

      <a href="/emergency-kits" class="sb-visual-card">
        <div class="sb-visual-img">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&q=80&fit=crop" alt="Emergency kits" />
          <div class="sb-visual-overlay"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="sb-visual-label">Emergency Kits →</div>
      </a>

      <a href="/backup-power" class="sb-visual-card">
        <div class="sb-visual-img">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1548438294-1ad5d5f4f063?w=300&q=80&fit=crop" alt="Backup power" />
          <div class="sb-visual-overlay"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="sb-visual-label">Backup Power Guide →</div>
      </a>

      <div class="sb-card sb-cta">
        <h4>Winter Weather Alerts</h4>
        <p>Sign up for NOAA weather alerts for your area before storm season.</p>
        <a href="https://www.weather.gov" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-outline" style="margin-top:14px; font-size:0.85rem; width:100%; text-align:center; display:block;">
          NOAA Weather Service →
        </a>
      </div>
    </aside>

  </div>

</BaseLayout>

<script>
  const sections = ['risks','pipes','heating','icedams','power','supplies','checklist']
  const tabs = document.querySelectorAll('.section-tabs .tab')
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
    entries.forEach(entry => {
      if (entry.isIntersecting) {
        tabs.forEach(t => t.classList.remove('active'))
        const activeTab = document.querySelector(`.tab[href="#${entry.target.id}"]`)
        if (activeTab) activeTab.classList.add('active')
      }
    })
  }, { rootMargin: '-20% 0px -70% 0px' })
  sections.forEach(id => { const el = document.getElementById(id); if (el) observer.observe(el) })
</script>

<style>
  .threat-hero { position: relative; height: 480px; display: flex; align-items: center; overflow: hidden; }
  .hero-img-wrap { position: absolute; inset: 0; z-index: 0; }
  .hero-img { width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; object-position: center; }
  .hero-overlay { position: absolute; inset: 0; background: linear-gradient(to right, rgba(13,35,56,0.92) 0%, rgba(13,35,56,0.65) 60%, rgba(13,35,56,0.3) 100%); }
  .hero-content { position: relative; z-index: 1; max-width: 640px; color: white; }
  .hero-label { font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: #A8CEDF; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .hero-content h1 { color: white; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .hero-sub { font-size: 1.05rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.8); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 32px; max-width: 560px; }
  .hero-actions { display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-text { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.75); font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 500; text-decoration: none; transition: color 0.15s; }
  .btn-text:hover { color: white; text-decoration: none; }

  .key-facts { background: var(--off-white); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 24px 0; }
  .facts-row { display: flex; align-items: center; }
  .fact { flex: 1; padding: 0 32px; }
  .fact:first-child { padding-left: 0; }
  .fact-value { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--navy); margin-bottom: 3px; }
  .fact-label { font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--text-light); }
  .fact-divider { width: 2px; height: 36px; background: var(--border); flex-shrink: 0; }

  .section-tabs { background: white; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border); position: sticky; top: 68px; z-index: 90; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.06); }
  .tabs-row { display: flex; overflow-x: auto; scrollbar-width: none; }
  .tabs-row::-webkit-scrollbar { display: none; }
  .tab { font-size: 0.82rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-mid); padding: 14px 20px; white-space: nowrap; text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 3px solid transparent; margin-bottom: -2px; transition: all 0.15s; border-right: 1.5px solid var(--border); }
  .tab:last-child { border-right: none; }
  .tab:hover { color: var(--sky); background: var(--sky-light); text-decoration: none; }
  .tab.active { color: var(--sky); border-bottom-color: var(--sky); font-weight: 600; background: var(--sky-light); }

  .page-layout { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 280px; gap: 56px; padding-top: 48px; padding-bottom: 96px; align-items: start; }
  .lead { font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text-mid); margin-bottom: 32px; }
  .article p { color: #333; line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .article h3 { margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: var(--navy); }

  .part-heading { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 16px; margin: 48px 0 24px; padding-bottom: 16px; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--navy); scroll-margin-top: 140px; }
  .part-number { background: var(--navy); color: white; font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; padding: 4px 10px; border-radius: 4px; white-space: nowrap; }
  .part-title { font-size: 1.4rem; color: var(--navy); margin: 0; }

  .section-block { margin-top: 48px; padding-top: 48px; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); scroll-margin-top: 140px; }
  .section-block h2 { color: var(--navy); margin-bottom: 20px; font-size: 1.4rem; }

  .risk-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 16px; margin: 24px 0 0; }
  .risk-item { background: var(--off-white); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 24px 16px; text-align: center; }
  .risk-icon-wrap { width: 56px; height: 56px; margin: 0 auto 14px; }
  .risk-icon-wrap svg { width: 100%; height: 100%; }
  .risk-item h3 { font-size: 0.95rem; margin: 0 0 8px; color: var(--navy); }
  .risk-item p { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--text-mid); line-height: 1.5; margin: 0; }

  .steps { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px; margin: 24px 0; }
  .step { display: flex; gap: 16px; align-items: flex-start; }
  .step-num { background: var(--sky); color: white; width: 30px; height: 30px; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.85rem; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px; }
  .step strong { display: block; margin-bottom: 3px; color: var(--navy); }
  .step p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--text-mid); }

